    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="620"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.0145/12</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 975</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-11">January 11,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sir: Reference is made to your Embassy’s despatch No. 3084 of November 27,
                        1935,<note n="61" xml:id="d620fn61">Not printed.</note> with which was
                    enclosed the official text, with translation, of the Presidential Decree of
                    August 29, 1935, published in the <hi rend="italic">Diario Oficial</hi> of
                    August 31, 1935, the stated object of which decree is to establish the breadth
                    of Mexican territorial waters at nine nautical miles.</p>
                <pb facs="0858" n="759" xml:id="pg_759"/>
                <p>It is desired that you advise the Mexican Foreign Office in writing that your
                    Government reserves all rights of whatever nature so far as concerns any effects
                    upon American commerce from enforcement of this legislation purporting to amend
                    existing law so as to extend the territorial waters of Mexico from three miles
                    in breadth to nine miles.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
